1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Health – Pediatric Hospital Overstay Patients and Workgroup on
3 Children in Unlicensed Settings and Pediatric Overstays
4 FOR the purpose of specifying that the scope of the Maryland Mental Health and Substance
5 Use Disorder Registry and Referral System includes both private and State inpatient
6 and outpatient mental health and substance use services; requiring the Maryland
7 Department of Health, in coordination with the Department of Human Services, to
8 ensure pediatric hospital overstay patients are placed in the least restrictive setting
9 when clinically indicated and when possible; authorizing a hospital to concurrently
10 explore in–State and out–of–state placements for pediatric hospital overstay
11 patients; establishing the requiring the Maryland Department of Health and the
12 Department of Human Services to establish a Pediatric Hospital Overstay
13 Coordinator within the Governor’s Office for Children; requiring the Maryland
14 Department of Health to conduct a certain study and review of residential treatment
15 center and respite facility rates; each department; establishing the Workgroup on
16 Children in Unlicensed Settings and Pediatric Overstays in the State; and generally
17 relating to pediatric hospital overstay patients and children in unlicensed settings.
